Ah, perfect\emdash that clarifies exactly how the logistics layer should be abstracted. So visually the player sees drones zipping between ships, but under the hood it\rquote s really a resource pipeline between storage nodes and production queues. Here\rquote s how I\rquote d structure it cleanly in your system:\par
\par
\f2 1\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f0  Drone Ports / Cargo Access Points\par
Each ship defines drone ports as special InteriorBlock types or attach points on the hull.\par
\par
Properties:\par
\par
ConnectedStorage: reference to internal cargo / factory output\par
\par
PortType: input/output (or bidirectional)\par
\par
MaxThroughput: limits drone traffic per tick for simulation purposes\par
\par
Drones don\f1\rquote\f0 t need pathfinding inside ship, just a \f1\ldblquote\f0 virtual lane\f1\rdblquote  \f0 connecting cargo \f4\u8594?\f1  \f0 drone port \f4\u8594?\f1  \f0 target ship port.\par
\par
Only active in fleet deploy mode.\par
\par
\f2 2\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f0  Resource Transfer Logic\par
Drones are just visual proxies:\par
\par
AI checks manufacturing queue or fleet request.\par
\par
Resources are pulled from ConnectedStorage.\par
\par
Drones animate from source port to target port.\par
\par
On arrival, resources are deposited into target ship\f1\rquote\f0 s storage or manufacturing input.\par
\par
The actual resource count is updated immediately, not waiting for animation to finish\f1\emdash animation is purely cosmetic.\par
\par
\f2 3\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f0  Manufacturing Chain Integration\par
Inside each ship:\par
\par
FactoryBlocks consume resources from storage connected to drone ports.\par
\par
Output items are deposited into output storage connected to drone ports.\par
\par
Fleet AI issues resource requests:\par
\par
Example: \f1\ldblquote\f0 Mining ship brings 100 fuel \f4\u8594?\f1  \f0 Mother ship \f4\u8594?\f1  \f0 Factory converts 100 ore to 10 components \f4\u8594?\f1  \f0 Components sent to combat ship.\f1\rdblquote\f0\par
\par
This keeps player-visible drones but maintains real-time resource simulation internally.\par
\par
\f2 4\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f0  Fleet Deploy Mode Toggle\par
Drones and resource transfers only exist in fleet deploy mode.\par
\par
Outside deploy mode (player controlling ship alone):\par
\par
Cargo interaction is internal only, drones inactive.\par
\par
No need for cross-ship logistics calculations.\par
\par
Internally:\par
\par
if FleetDeployMode:\par
    activate drone transfer system\par
else:\par
    ignore drone ports\par
