\f2 1\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f0  Data Structure: ModuleSize + SlotGrid Logic\par
We want a flexible, tiered system where modules occupy slots in a ship grid, scale properly, and allow filling gaps dynamically.\par
\par
struct ModuleSlot \{\par
    Vector3 position;          // Grid position in ship (X, Y, Z)\par
    ModuleSize size;           // XS, S, M, L, XL, XXL\par
    ModuleType type;           // Factory, Storage, Elevator, Cockpit, Hangar, DronePort\par
    bool occupied;             // Is this slot already filled\par
    ModuleID moduleID;         // Unique module reference\par
    vector<ModuleSlot*> neighbors; // Connected slots for traversal/AI\par
\};\par
\par
enum ModuleSize \{ XS, S, M, L, XL, XXL \};\par
\par
struct Module \{\par
    ModuleID id;\par
    ModuleType type;\par
    ModuleSize size;\par
    Vector3 dimensions;        // in grid units (calculated from size)\par
    vector<ModuleSlot*> slots; // slots it occupies\par
    TierLevel tier;            // Tiny \f4\u8594?\f1  \f0 Shuttle \f4\u8594?\f1  \f0 Frigate \f4\u8594?\f1  \f0 Cruiser \f4\u8594?\f1  \f0 Capital\par
    bool expandable;           // Can module be replaced or upgraded\par
\};\par
SlotGrid Logic:\par
\par
Ship is divided into a 3D grid of slots.\par
\par
Each module occupies N slots according to its size.\par
\par
Adjacent free slots can be filled with smaller modules.\par
\par
Traversal nodes (doors, ramps, ladders, elevators) are attached to slots.\par
\par
Symmetry is enforced by mirroring slot assignments where needed.\par
\par
\f2 2\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f0  Density-Field Update Rules for Incremental Module Insertion\par
We need incremental hull updates as modules are added to the ship.\par
\par
Stepwise Algorithm\par
Module Placement\par
\par
Check if desired slots are free.\par
\par
Check adjacency rules (e.g., elevator must connect all floors, ramps must slope correctly).\par
\par
Reserve slots.\par
\par
Density Contribution\par
\par
Each module adds density to grid voxels:\par
\par
Solid walls = 1.0\par
Interior air = 0.0\par
Smooth edges/ramps = 0.5\par
Hull Blending\par
\par
Merge density contributions:\par
\par
voxelDensity(x,y,z) = max(previousDensity, moduleDensity)\par
Apply smoothing kernel along module edges to avoid jagged hull.\par
\par
Symmetry Enforcement\par
\par
Mirror density contribution along ship symmetry axes.\par
\par
Dynamic Rebuild\par
\par
Only affected hull region rebuilt (incremental marching cubes/isosurface update).\par
\par
Traversal Graph Update\par
\par
Update nodes for corridors, doors, ramps, ladders, elevators connected to module slots.\par
\par
AI/drone pathfinding recalculated in affected region.\par
