Perfect \emdash  now we can design the Blueprint-style visual scripting integration for your in-game Dev World. This system will let you connect NPC triggers, AI asset spawns, ship module events, and PCG regeneration in a node-based interface, fully usable in the ToolingLayer overlay.\par
\par
1. Blueprint Node System Concept\par
Goal: Allow designers to visually \ldblquote wire together\rdblquote  events, actions, and conditions, like Unreal Engine Blueprints, directly in the Dev Station.\par
\par
Node Types\par
Node Type\tab Purpose\par
Event\tab Triggers: OnEnterRoom, OnSpawn, OnDock, OnPlayerInteract\par
Action\tab MoveShip, AttachModule, SpawnNPC, PlayAnimation, RegeneratePCG\par
Condition\tab DistanceCheck, ResourceCheck, RandomChance, TaskCompleted\par
Variable\tab Store values for logic: integers, floats, booleans, entity references\par
Function\tab Reusable sequences of nodes for complex behaviors\par
2. Node & Connection Skeleton\par
struct BlueprintNode\par
\{\par
    std::string id;\par
    std::string type; // Event, Action, Condition\par
    std::unordered_map<std::string, std::string> parameters; // e.g., \{"TargetEntity":"Ship01"\}\par
    std::vector<std::string> outputNodeIds; // connected nodes\par
\};\par
\par
class BlueprintGraph\par
\{\par
public:\par
    std::unordered_map<std::string, BlueprintNode> nodes;\par
\par
    void AddNode(const BlueprintNode& node);\par
    void RemoveNode(const std::string& nodeId);\par
    void ConnectNodes(const std::string& fromNode, const std::string& toNode);\par
    void ExecuteNode(const std::string& nodeId); // runs logic recursively\par
\};\par
Each node has parameters and can connect to multiple outputs.\par
\par
Execution is depth-first, optional cycle detection to avoid infinite loops.\par
\par
3. Example Use Case in Hangar\par
Scenario: Player enters a ship hangar \u8594? NPC spawns \u8594? NPC interacts with ship \u8594? PCG regeneration triggered.\par
\par
Node Graph\par
Event Node: OnPlayerEnterRoom \u8594? triggers output.\par
\par
Action Node: SpawnNPC \u8594? spawns engineer NPC.\par
\par
Action Node: AttachModule \u8594? engineer attaches module to ship.\par
\par
Action Node: RegeneratePCG \u8594? updates PCGPreview to reflect edits.\par
\par
Condition Node: TaskCompleted \u8594? only triggers RegeneratePCG if ship edits done.\par
\par
Execution Flow:\par
\par
OnPlayerEnterRoom -> SpawnNPC -> AttachModule -> (TaskCompleted?) -> RegeneratePCG\par
4. Blueprint Execution Example\par
void BlueprintGraph::ExecuteNode(const std::string& nodeId)\par
\{\par
    auto it = nodes.find(nodeId);\par
    if (it == nodes.end()) return;\par
\par
    BlueprintNode& node = it->second;\par
\par
    if (node.type == "Event")\par
    \{\par
        // Events may be triggered by ToolingLayer overlay\par
    \}\par
    else if (node.type == "Action")\par
    \{\par
        if (node.parameters["ActionType"] == "SpawnNPC")\par
        \{\par
            AIAssetRequest request;\par
            request.prompt = node.parameters["NPCType"];\par
            request.position[0] = std::stof(node.parameters["PosX"]);\par
            request.position[1] = std::stof(node.parameters["PosY"]);\par
            request.position[2] = std::stof(node.parameters["PosZ"]);\par
            \par
            Room* room = DevStation::Get().GetRoom(std::stoi(node.parameters["Floor"]));\par
            AIAssetSpawner::Get().SpawnInRoom(request, *room);\par
        \}\par
        else if (node.parameters["ActionType"] == "RegeneratePCG")\par
        \{\par
            PCGPreview::Get().RefreshScene();\par
        \}\par
        // add more ActionType handlers as needed\par
    \}\par
    else if (node.type == "Condition")\par
    \{\par
        if (node.parameters["ConditionType"] == "TaskCompleted")\par
        \{\par
            Room* room = DevStation::Get().GetRoom(std::stoi(node.parameters["Floor"]));\par
            bool complete = room->todoList.AllTasksCompleted();\par
            if (!complete) return; // stop execution\par
        \}\par
    \}\par
\par
    // Execute connected nodes recursively\par
    for (auto& outId : node.outputNodeIds)\par
        ExecuteNode(outId);\par
\}\par
