\f2 2\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f6  ToolingLayer Class Structure\par
// Base abstraction for any editor tool\par
class ITool\par
\{\par
public:\par
    virtual ~ITool() = default;\par
    virtual void Activate() = 0;\par
    virtual void Deactivate() = 0;\par
    virtual void Update(float deltaTime) = 0;\par
\};\par
\par
// Core Tooling Layer\par
class ToolingLayer\par
\{\par
private:\par
    std::vector<std::unique_ptr<ITool>> activeTools;\par
\par
public:\par
    void RegisterTool(std::unique_ptr<ITool> tool);\par
    void UnregisterTool(ITool* tool);\par
    void UpdateTools(float deltaTime);\par
\};\par
Key Points:\par
\par
All editor tools (e.g., StarSystemEditor, ShipModuleEditor) implement ITool.\par
\par
ToolingLayer manages activation/deactivation and updates.\par
\par
Keeps editor code isolated from game runtime logic.\par
\par
\f2 3\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f6  EditorCommandBus Architecture\par
// Commands are decoupled from their execution context\par
struct ICommand\par
\{\par
    virtual ~ICommand() = default;\par
    virtual void Execute() = 0;\par
\};\par
\par
// Concrete commands\par
class CreateStarSystemCommand : public ICommand\par
\{\par
public:\par
    void Execute() override;\par
\};\par
\par
// Bus decouples sender/receiver\par
class EditorCommandBus\par
\{\par
private:\par
    std::queue<std::unique_ptr<ICommand>> commandQueue;\par
\par
public:\par
    void PostCommand(std::unique_ptr<ICommand> cmd);\par
    void ProcessCommands();\par
\};\par
Highlights:\par
\par
Commands are fully decoupled; supports undo/redo in the future.\par
\par
Editor/Tooling systems post commands; bus handles execution.\par
\par
Enables batching and deferred execution safely.\par
\par
\f2 4\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f6  Hardened RuntimeBootstrap\par
Objective: Single entrypoint with zero duplicated boot logic.\par
\par
class RuntimeBootstrap\par
\{\par
private:\par
    void LoadCoreSystems();\par
    void LoadPlatformSystems(); // Editor / Server / Runtime\par
    void LoadGameModules();\par
\par
public:\par
    void Initialize(RuntimeMode mode); // Enum: Editor, Game, Server\par
\};\par
Workflow:\par
\par
Initialize() called with mode.\par
\par
Core systems load (logging, config, ECS, event bus).\par
\par
Platform-specific systems load without duplicating core initialization.\par
\par
Game modules initialize (ships, AI, PCG).\par
\par
Benefits:\par
\par
Editor, Runtime, and Server all share the same core boot logic.\par
\par
Mode-specific differences are abstracted and isolated.\par
\par
Simplifies maintenance and future scaling.\par
\par
