The Test Solar System does not directly copy layouts into player systems.\par
\par
Instead it produces:\par
\par
PCG Template Weights\par
+ Spatial Distribution Rules\par
+ Structural Relationship Constraints\par
+ Behavioral Modifiers\par
+ Parameter Ranges\par
+ Bias Coefficients\par
Player systems are then generated from:\par
\par
FinalOutput = Seed \f7\u8853? \f6 BasePCG \f7\u8853? \f6 TemplateWeights \f7\u8853? \f6 DeltaEdits \f7\u8853? \f6 RandomVariance\par
Where:\par
\par
\f7\u8853? \f6 = layered procedural merge operator\par
\par
Seed = player world seed\par
\par
BasePCG = original generation logic\par
\par
TemplateWeights = learned from Test System\par
\par
DeltaEdits = dev modifications\par
\par
RandomVariance = controlled entropy\par
\par
\f2 2\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f6  Inheritance Layers\par
Layer 0 \f7\emdash  \f6 Base Generator\par
Your original PCG math:\par
\par
Example:\par
\par
planetDistance = random(seed) * maxDistance\par
stationCount = random(seed) % 5\par
asteroidDensity = noise(seed)\par
This layer always exists.\par
\par
Layer 1 \f7\emdash  \f6 Structural Weight Extraction\par
From Test Solar System we calculate:\par
\par
A) Spatial Frequency Matrix\par
For each asset type:\par
\par
frequency(type) = count(type) / totalAssets\par
Example:\par
\par
rockyPlanet: 0.35\par
gasGiant: 0.15\par
militaryStation: 0.10\par
asteroidField: 0.25\par
Future PCG biases toward these ratios.\par
\par
B) Radial Distribution Curve\par
We compute average distance from star per type:\par
\par
avgDistance(type) = \u931?(distanceFromStar) / count\par
We also compute variance:\par
\par
variance(type) = \u931?((distance - avgDistance)^2) / count\par
Future systems inherit that distribution curve.\par
\par
So if you place gas giants far out?\par
All generated systems bias gas giants outward.\par
\par
C) Structural Relationship Matrix\par
We record relationships:\par
\par
P(station | planetType)\par
P(militaryStation | lavaPlanet)\par
P(miningStation | asteroidField)\par
Example:\par
\par
P(miningStation | asteroidField) = 0.82\par
P(militaryStation | lavaPlanet) = 0.64\par
Future PCG honors these relationship weights.\par
\par
\f2 3\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f6  Parameter Range Learning\par
For any editable parameter:\par
\par
enginePower\par
gravity\par
atmosphereDensity\par
moduleSize\par
hangarScale\par
We extract:\par
\par
minObserved\par
maxObserved\par
mean\par
stdDeviation\par
Then clamp PCG to:\par
\par
newValue = clamp(\par
    randomGaussian(mean, stdDev),\par
    minObserved,\par
    maxObserved\par
)\par
This prevents future worlds from generating nonsense values outside your tuned bounds.\par
\par
\f2 4\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f6  DeltaEdits as Bias Multipliers\par
Each edit produces:\par
\par
deltaWeight = importanceFactor \'d7 recencyFactor\par
Where:\par
\par
importanceFactor = manualWeight (0\f7\endash\f6 1)\par
recencyFactor = e^(\f7\u8722?\f6\u955? \'d7 versionDistance)\par
So newer edits weigh more unless locked.\par
\par
Final bias applied as:\par
\par
adjustedProbability = baseProbability \'d7 (1 + deltaWeight)\par
\f2 5\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f6  Geometry Learning (Shape Influence)\par
We can also extract:\par
\par
A) Bounding Box Profiles\par
avgShipLength\par
avgStationHeight\par
avgPlanetScale\par
B) Proportional Ratios\par
engineSize / hullSize\par
hangarWidth / shipLength\par
turretCount / shipClass\par
Future PCG generates using:\par
\par
newRatio = randomGaussian(observedMeanRatio, ratioVariance)\par
This makes future content match your aesthetic language.\par
\par
\f2 6\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f6  Noise Bias Modulation\par
Your procedural noise functions can be altered by:\par
\par
noiseAmplitude *= learnedAmplitudeFactor\par
noiseFrequency *= learnedFrequencyFactor\par
So if you smooth terrain in the Test System:\par
Future planets generate smoother.\par
\par
\f2 7\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f6  Behavioral Inheritance\par
For AI:\par
\par
We log:\par
\par
engagementDistance\par
fleetSize\par
stationDefenseCount\par
Future NPC systems generate using:\par
\par
behaviorParameter = baseValue \'d7 learnedMultiplier\par
\f2 8\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f6  Complete Mathematical Model\par
Full generation pipeline:\par
\par
function GenerateSystem(seed):\par
\par
    base = BasePCG(seed)\par
\par
    templateWeights = ExtractTemplateWeights(TestSolarSystem)\par
\par
    biasedStructure = ApplyStructuralBias(base.structure, templateWeights)\par
\par
    biasedParameters = ApplyParameterLearning(base.parameters, templateWeights)\par
\par
    biasedGeometry = ApplyRatioLearning(base.geometry, templateWeights)\par
\par
    biasedBehavior = ApplyBehaviorModifiers(base.behavior, templateWeights)\par
\par
    finalSystem = MergeWithVariance(\par
        biasedStructure,\par
        biasedParameters,\par
        biasedGeometry,\par
        biasedBehavior,\par
        entropy(seed)\par
    )\par
\par
    return finalSystem\par
\f2 9\u-497?\f3\u8419?\f6  Safeguards\par
To prevent overfitting:\par
\par
Introduce entropy floor:\par
\par
entropyFloor = 0.15\par
finalVariance = max(entropyFloor, computedVariance)\par
And bias cap:\par
\par
biasClamp = 0.65\par
adjustedProbability = clamp(adjustedProbability, 0, biasClamp)\par
So PCG never becomes a clone of Test System.\par
