\f2\u-10179?\u-8464?\u-497?\f7  \f6 NovaForge \f7\emdash  \f6 Design Philosophy\par
NovaForge is a procedural legend engine, not a scripted game.\par
\par
The goal is not to tell the player a story \f7\emdash\f6\par
it is to create the conditions where stories emerge naturally,\par
and then allow the universe to remember them.\par
\par
Core Pillars\par
Truthful Systems\par
The game never fakes outcomes. Physics, AI, and simulation always resolve honestly.\par
\par
Structured Chaos\par
Campaigns provide pacing and intent without dictating results.\par
\par
Legend Over Progression\par
Player behavior shapes future worlds through bias and probability, not stat inflation.\par
\par
Memory With Restraint\par
The game remembers patterns, not moments. Forgetting is intentional.\par
\par
What NovaForge Is Not\par
Not a scripted narrative game\par
\par
Not a power-fantasy escalation treadmill\par
\par
Not a sandbox without meaning\par
\par
Contribution Rules (Important)\par
When adding features:\par
\par
\f3\u10060?\f7  \f6 Do not script outcomes\par
\par
\f3\u10060?\f7  \f6 Do not hard-code hero moments\par
\par
\f3\u10060?\f7  \f6 Do not add permanent player penalties\par
\par
\f3\u9989?\f7  \f6 Prefer data-driven bias\par
\par
\f3\u9989?\f7  \f6 Prefer probability over certainty\par
\par
\f3\u9989?\f7  \f6 Prefer systems that interact, not override\par
\par
If a feature does not support legend formation, world bias, or emergent storytelling, it does not belong in NovaForge.\par
\par
